choices.text:
the referendum that was carried out on September 16th 2015 67% of Rwandan people were in favor of amending the Constitution which led to certain changes including changing the age limit for the President and Vice President to enable President Kagame to run for another term of office after he is no longer allowed in office doen to the set maximum number of years allowed as the President. A few days after the referendum, President Kagame was sworn in as a president for another 7 years.

The president during his inauguration speech called for unity and peace among Rwandans of different political ideologies promising them that they have nothing to do with what the constitution has just decided.

The president expressed his condolences to all the eight soldiers who lost their life in two separate attacks which happened in North Congo and Central Kenya.

During his speech, the President was backed by the speaker of the house which set the peace in the parliament, as we have seen because Rwanda has been experiencing a lot of challenges in the house but now the speaker of the house Paul Kagame is having a strong say in the house. During ongoing, impeachment of AG to be, the speaker of the parliament and most powerful man in Rwanda Margaret who is the younger sister of Kagame has used her role as a speaker to put a stop to their decision to impeach the Attorney General after they were presented with facts in order to challenge their decision. This indicates an increased role of women in Rwandan politics.
